00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,000
 The End

2
00:00:02,000 --> 00:00:04,000
 The End

3
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:06,000
 The End

4
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:08,000
 The End

5
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:13,000
 Isaac Hickentude, do you take Nigel to be your husband?

6
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:17,000
 I don't. And you couldn't have told me this an hour ago.

7
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:22,000
 Her name is Patience. She's a lady that lives in the ground.

8
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:24,000
 What? Who was that?

9
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:26,000
 We were once stuck and whole.

10
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:28,000
 We decided we had to join hands

11
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:30,500
 and navigate our way through the dirt

12
00:00:30,500 --> 00:00:32,000
 to the Woodstone basement.

13
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:34,000
 We agreed that Sass would lead the way,

14
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:36,000
 then Thor, then myself.

15
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:37,500
 There was another ghost in the hole with us.

16
00:00:37,500 --> 00:00:39,000
 Her name was Patience. She was a Puritan.

17
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:40,000
 What happened to her?

18
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:42,500
 Isaac sneezed and let go of Patience's hand.

19
00:00:42,500 --> 00:00:44,500
 For all we know, she's still out there roaming.

20
00:00:44,500 --> 00:00:46,500
 So you're telling me there's a Puritan woman

21
00:00:46,500 --> 00:00:49,500
 just out there wandering around in the dirt?

22
00:00:49,500 --> 00:00:50,500
 Yes.

23
00:00:50,500 --> 00:00:52,500
 Mm-mm. I don't like that one bit.

24
00:00:52,500 --> 00:00:55,000
 You really should have invited us to the wedding, Isaac.

25
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:57,000
 He's here, Patience.

26
00:00:57,000 --> 00:00:58,000
 God bless you.

27
00:00:58,000 --> 00:00:59,000
 Oh!

28
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:02,000
 Patience.

29
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:07,000
 The council has met, and we've decided that we'd like you to leave the community.

30
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:10,000
 What? But I'm the most pious among us.

31
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:14,000
 Who experiences less joy than I? Who is more severe?

32
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:17,000
 You are joyless and severe, I agree.

33
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:21,000
 But even for us, Puritans are such a thing as too severe.

34
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:24,000
 I mean, you wanted us to execute Miss Elizabeth Prue.

35
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:27,299
 She was talking to a doll, tis surely a sign of witchcraft.

36
00:01:27,299 --> 00:01:28,299
 She's five.

37
00:01:28,299 --> 00:01:30,500
 And on a path most dark.

38
00:01:30,500 --> 00:01:33,000
 The point is you have to leave, I'm sorry.

39
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:35,300
 Then fine.

40
00:01:35,300 --> 00:01:38,300
 I shall start my own colony,

41
00:01:38,300 --> 00:01:41,300
 where there will be no smiling, no laughter,

42
00:01:41,300 --> 00:01:45,300
 and all the handles of the butter churns shall be rough-hewn,

43
00:01:45,300 --> 00:01:50,300
 so that thou shalt feel the pain of sin with every stroke.

44
00:01:50,300 --> 00:01:52,300
 Well,

45
00:01:52,300 --> 00:01:55,000
 I think people are going to really enjoy that.

46
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:57,140
 Or not enjoy it, whatever you wish.

47
00:01:57,140 --> 00:02:01,140
 Anyway, banishment next.

48
00:02:01,140 --> 00:02:11,659
 Oh, man, I feel bad about Isaac leaving Nigel at the altar last night.

49
00:02:11,659 --> 00:02:13,680
 But what a show.

50
00:02:13,680 --> 00:02:14,680
 Indeed.

51
00:02:14,680 --> 00:02:18,500
 At least it was a break from the crushing mundanity of our bleak existence.

52
00:02:18,500 --> 00:02:21,500
 Okay, the water bill this month is unusually high.

53
00:02:21,500 --> 00:02:23,340
 Just like that. We're back.

54
00:02:23,340 --> 00:02:25,539
 Jay, have you been taking long showers or something?

55
00:02:25,539 --> 00:02:27,300
 You think I'm taking long showers?

56
00:02:27,300 --> 00:02:29,840
 I got a bunch of invisible people creeping on me.

57
00:02:29,840 --> 00:02:31,379
 I wear a bathing suit in there.

58
00:02:31,379 --> 00:02:33,419
 People are so uptight about nudity.

59
00:02:33,419 --> 00:02:35,539
 And the cult we used to take group showers.

60
00:02:35,539 --> 00:02:38,180
 We really help to clean those hard-to-reach places.

61
00:02:38,180 --> 00:02:40,020
 Quick, some of them were water built up?

62
00:02:40,020 --> 00:02:43,479
 Hey, guys. Got those tile samples for the restaurant.

63
00:02:43,479 --> 00:02:45,520
 Mark and I just went to the hardware store.

64
00:02:45,520 --> 00:02:47,520
 Because I can leave the property?

65
00:02:47,520 --> 00:02:48,520
 We know, Pete.

66
00:02:48,520 --> 00:02:50,759
 This one's perfect. Right here. Final answer. Lock it in.

67
00:02:50,759 --> 00:02:52,299
 Well, okay. That was easy.

68
00:02:52,299 --> 00:02:54,340
 It's usually a whole weird song and dance with you two.

69
00:02:54,340 --> 00:02:56,639
 Well, we should confirm it with our investor.

70
00:02:56,639 --> 00:02:58,259
 Right, our silent partner.

71
00:02:58,259 --> 00:03:00,939
 But do you really think he needs to weigh in on such a little thing?

72
00:03:00,939 --> 00:03:03,479
 Yes, I think he would be very upset if we didn't loop him in.

73
00:03:03,479 --> 00:03:05,399
 Yeah, that's more what I expected.

74
00:03:05,399 --> 00:03:07,239
 Anyway, our supplier said he's almost out of these,

75
00:03:07,239 --> 00:03:09,739
 so if we want them, we gotta act fast.

76
00:03:09,739 --> 00:03:12,620
 See? So let's ask Isaac, okay? Is he in here?

77
00:03:12,620 --> 00:03:14,579
 No. Have any of you guys seen him?

78
00:03:14,579 --> 00:03:17,419
 Hmm, no. He must still be moping in this room.

79
00:03:17,419 --> 00:03:19,780
 Oh, poor guy. But it was exciting for us.

80
00:03:19,780 --> 00:03:22,120
 Oh, the drama! The smell of the hors d'oeuvres!

81
00:03:22,120 --> 00:03:24,280
 The camaraderie, the sharing of the soul.

82
00:03:24,280 --> 00:03:25,780
 And she's back on group showers.

83
00:03:25,780 --> 00:03:26,780
 He wasn't at the hardware store,

84
00:03:26,780 --> 00:03:29,280
 because he can't leave the property, which I can.

85
00:03:29,280 --> 00:03:30,780
 What'd they say?

86
00:03:30,780 --> 00:03:33,280
 They haven't seen him. I hope he's doing okay.

87
00:03:33,280 --> 00:03:34,780
 I'm sure he's fine.

88
00:03:34,780 --> 00:03:36,780
 Okay, okay, you know what?

89
00:03:36,780 --> 00:03:38,780
 Let's just address the elephant in the room.

90
00:03:38,780 --> 00:03:39,780
 You're upset with me.

91
00:03:39,780 --> 00:03:41,780
 Patience! Patience!

92
00:03:41,780 --> 00:03:42,780
 That's new.

93
00:03:42,780 --> 00:03:45,780
 Thou didst abandon me.

94
00:03:45,780 --> 00:03:47,780
 It was an accident!

95
00:03:47,780 --> 00:03:50,240
 I had to sneeze, and so I covered my nose.

96
00:03:50,400 --> 00:03:53,800
 And in doing so, I did let go of your hand

97
00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:55,420
 and abandoned you to the dirt.

98
00:03:55,680 --> 00:03:57,139
 The point is, I was wrong.

99
00:03:58,580 --> 00:03:59,660
 And I apologize.

100
00:04:00,520 --> 00:04:03,000
 Tis my intention to push thee into the dirt

101
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:05,719
 such that thou may know the century of suffering

102
00:04:05,719 --> 00:04:06,960
 patience has endured.

103
00:04:07,759 --> 00:04:08,379
 What?

104
00:04:08,539 --> 00:04:08,860
 Patience!

105
00:04:10,219 --> 00:04:10,740
 Hey.

106
00:04:11,599 --> 00:04:14,340
 Sorry, um, have you seen Isaac?

107
00:04:14,340 --> 00:04:19,000
 The marksman who only yesterday pierced my heart for a second time?

108
00:04:19,459 --> 00:04:20,920
 No, I can't say that I have.

109
00:04:21,519 --> 00:04:25,879
 But, in a grander sense, I'm not sure I've ever seen the real Isaac.

110
00:04:26,459 --> 00:04:28,800
 I'm sorry, Nigel. This is really hard.

111
00:04:29,280 --> 00:04:32,420
 Nigel's still living in the house? I thought he would have slunk back to the shed.

112
00:04:33,639 --> 00:04:34,560
 Dammit, Jay.

113
00:04:34,759 --> 00:04:37,519
 What? Didn't Isaac, like, totally ditch him at the altar?

114
00:04:39,220 --> 00:04:41,500
 Well, we'll leave you alone.

115
00:04:41,500 --> 00:04:45,259
 and those of us who possess the ability to close doors will do so.

116
00:04:45,259 --> 00:04:47,459
 No!

117
00:04:47,459 --> 00:04:49,459
 Can you turn on the TV already?

118
00:04:49,459 --> 00:04:51,100
 It's not called 45 minutes.

119
00:04:51,100 --> 00:04:52,379
 Someone watch the full 60.

120
00:04:52,379 --> 00:04:54,800
 Okay, it's not just like pressing a button.

121
00:04:54,800 --> 00:04:55,800
 I mean, it is.

122
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:58,259
 But it's hard, and it's impressive that I can do it at all.

123
00:04:58,259 --> 00:05:01,100
 Possible Trevor's somehow growing weaker over time.

124
00:05:01,100 --> 00:05:03,439
 Legs are looking a little smaller.

125
00:05:03,439 --> 00:05:04,819
 What? No.

126
00:05:04,819 --> 00:05:06,939
 That's not even physically possible.

127
00:05:08,139 --> 00:05:10,319
 Hey, have you guys seen Isaac?

128
00:05:10,319 --> 00:05:11,319
 I haven't seen him.

129
00:05:11,319 --> 00:05:12,319
 Me neither.

130
00:05:12,319 --> 00:05:15,319
 Not since wet English went very bad.

131
00:05:19,319 --> 00:05:22,319
 Nancy, have you seen Isaac?

132
00:05:22,319 --> 00:05:23,319
 Isaac?

133
00:05:25,319 --> 00:05:29,319
 You know, now that you mention it, I think he said he was going for a stroll this morning.

134
00:05:29,319 --> 00:05:30,319
 Mm-hmm.

135
00:05:30,319 --> 00:05:34,319
 And I remember that because when he said stroll, I was looking at a bull and I was like,

136
00:05:34,319 --> 00:05:37,319
 whoa, stroll and bull, what are the chances?

137
00:05:39,319 --> 00:05:40,319
 What?

138
00:05:40,319 --> 00:05:41,579
 when he'd be back?

139
00:05:41,659 --> 00:05:44,860
 I'm sorry, I didn't get his life story.

140
00:05:44,920 --> 00:05:47,560
 Jeez, what's with the third degree, huh?

141
00:05:47,620 --> 00:05:48,959
 Why are you being so weird?

142
00:05:49,019 --> 00:05:50,360
 I'm not being weird.

143
00:05:50,420 --> 00:05:51,759
 You're being weird.

144
00:05:51,839 --> 00:05:55,159
 Quit taking your body issues out on me, chicken legs.

145
00:05:55,240 --> 00:05:56,399
 I don't have to taste it.

146
00:05:58,300 --> 00:05:59,379
 Interesting.

147
00:05:59,440 --> 00:06:01,300
 Nancy seems like she's hiding something.

148
00:06:01,379 --> 00:06:04,240
 Okay, you listen here, Nancy, and you listen good.

149
00:06:04,319 --> 00:06:05,379
 She left, Jay.

150
00:06:05,439 --> 00:06:08,219
 Why am I even along on this mission?

151
00:06:08,279 --> 00:06:10,319
 Please, Patience. I'm sorry.

152
00:06:10,319 --> 00:06:11,879
 I didn't mean to lose you.

153
00:06:11,879 --> 00:06:13,819
 I did look for you.

154
00:06:13,819 --> 00:06:17,019
 A few times I even ventured slightly into the dirt.

155
00:06:17,019 --> 00:06:18,560
 No, you wouldn't.

156
00:06:18,560 --> 00:06:20,159
 Not for patience.

157
00:06:20,159 --> 00:06:21,659
 Are you kidding?

158
00:06:21,659 --> 00:06:22,860
 I missed you.

159
00:06:22,860 --> 00:06:23,860
 We all missed you.

160
00:06:23,860 --> 00:06:26,980
 Me, Sass, Thor, the entire...

161
00:06:26,980 --> 00:06:28,779
 whole patrol.

162
00:06:28,779 --> 00:06:30,680
 I mean, we had some good times, right?

163
00:06:30,680 --> 00:06:34,680
 Remember when Thor tried to say the word supposedly

164
00:06:34,680 --> 00:06:37,680
 and instead said supposedly?

165
00:06:40,319 --> 00:06:42,420
 It was indeed quite amusing.

166
00:06:42,879 --> 00:06:45,680
 And I don't know about you, but I loved our time in the ditch.

167
00:06:46,360 --> 00:06:49,699
 I mean, who wouldn't enjoy staring at that gorgeous porcelain skin?

168
00:06:50,599 --> 00:06:52,420
 It is from the bloodletting that killed me.

169
00:06:53,240 --> 00:06:56,019
 I'm just glad we get to hang again.

170
00:06:56,519 --> 00:06:59,779
 Although, similarly to how Thor, Sass, and I miss being in the ditch with you,

171
00:06:59,860 --> 00:07:02,899
 I do fear I might miss being with them.

172
00:07:04,079 --> 00:07:05,579
 You see what I mean, Patience?

173
00:07:06,439 --> 00:07:08,399
 Isaac is lonely.

174
00:07:08,680 --> 00:07:09,100
 Exactly.

175
00:07:09,100 --> 00:07:11,660
 I miss my friends.

176
00:07:12,100 --> 00:07:13,980
 You can understand that, right?

177
00:07:14,240 --> 00:07:15,580
 Oh, patience understand.

178
00:07:16,640 --> 00:07:17,240
 Patience.

179
00:07:17,939 --> 00:07:18,540
 Patience.

180
00:07:18,820 --> 00:07:19,100
 Great.

181
00:07:20,300 --> 00:07:20,580
 Isaac.

182
00:07:21,480 --> 00:07:22,000
 Isaac.

183
00:07:23,240 --> 00:07:24,560
 Nancy, out with it.

184
00:07:24,680 --> 00:07:25,439
 What happened to Isaac?

185
00:07:25,680 --> 00:07:28,900
 I don't know why you guys are riding my leg about this.

186
00:07:28,980 --> 00:07:30,980
 I have no idea where he is.

187
00:07:31,460 --> 00:07:33,620
 Okay, I had promised not to say anything,

188
00:07:33,900 --> 00:07:35,540
 but Nancy already told me what happened.

189
00:07:35,540 --> 00:07:37,240
 You told him about patience?

190
00:07:37,820 --> 00:07:38,300
 Wait.

191
00:07:38,300 --> 00:07:40,300
 What happened with Patience?

192
00:07:40,300 --> 00:07:41,800
 Oh, damn it, Stuart.

193
00:07:41,800 --> 00:07:44,800
 You have to be the dumbest, most gullible piece of trash

194
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:47,300
 I've ever known, and I was married to the village idiot.

195
00:07:47,300 --> 00:07:48,800
 Come on, Nancy. What happened?

196
00:07:48,800 --> 00:07:52,800
 Okay. So yesterday, attracted by the pulsing bass

197
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:54,800
 from the wedding DJ's speakers,

198
00:07:54,800 --> 00:07:56,800
 Patience appeared through the wall.

199
00:07:56,800 --> 00:08:01,300
 She asked to speak to Isaac, so we arranged a meeting.

200
00:08:01,300 --> 00:08:03,300
 We thought she just wanted to yell at him a little.

201
00:08:03,300 --> 00:08:05,300
 We didn't know she was gonna drag him away.

202
00:08:05,300 --> 00:08:06,800
 It was very rude.

203
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:09,560
 We were mad about not being invited to the wedding,

204
00:08:09,560 --> 00:08:11,480
 but we didn't want this to happen!

205
00:08:11,480 --> 00:08:12,800
 Jay, a quick update.

206
00:08:12,800 --> 00:08:14,480
 Isaac was kidnapped by a Puritan ghost

207
00:08:14,480 --> 00:08:16,180
 who's been roaming the dirt for centuries,

208
00:08:16,180 --> 00:08:17,819
 waiting for a chance at revenge.

209
00:08:17,819 --> 00:08:19,319
 Oh, that's really gonna push back

210
00:08:19,319 --> 00:08:21,280
 and answer on these tiles.

211
00:08:21,280 --> 00:08:23,780
 Obviously, I'm also very concerned for Isaac.

212
00:08:23,780 --> 00:08:27,280
 Thor confused how Patience just take Isaac.

213
00:08:27,280 --> 00:08:30,360
 Not like she's strong enough to lift Isaac Dover's shoulder.

214
00:08:30,360 --> 00:08:32,700
 Probably be something you struggle with as well.

215
00:08:32,700 --> 00:08:36,060
 I broke a Thighmaster once, Thor. I broke it.

216
00:08:36,059 --> 00:08:38,319
 Patience is real stealth. I'll show you.

217
00:08:38,319 --> 00:08:41,359
 I'll be Patience, and Sass, you be Isaac, okay?

218
00:08:41,359 --> 00:08:43,359
 See, he was standing over there.

219
00:08:43,359 --> 00:08:44,939
 Right here?

220
00:08:44,939 --> 00:08:46,939
 Yep, but his back was to the wall.

221
00:08:46,939 --> 00:08:48,439
 Like this?

222
00:08:48,439 --> 00:08:50,939
 Exactly. Then all of a sudden...

223
00:08:50,939 --> 00:08:52,279
 Patience!

224
00:08:52,279 --> 00:08:54,279
 Whoo!

225
00:08:54,279 --> 00:08:58,379
 Okay, you gotta believe me.

226
00:08:58,379 --> 00:09:01,219
 We did not know that was gonna happen.

227
00:09:06,059 --> 00:09:08,059
 Surprise!

228
00:09:08,059 --> 00:09:10,059
 Patience! What is the meaning of this?

229
00:09:10,059 --> 00:09:12,059
 Thou didst say that thou missed thy friends.

230
00:09:12,059 --> 00:09:14,059
 Tis now a problem solved.

231
00:09:14,059 --> 00:09:17,059
 Wait, did I get kidnapped because Isaac said he was lonely?

232
00:09:17,059 --> 00:09:20,059
 No! I have been vastly misunderstood.

233
00:09:20,059 --> 00:09:22,059
 And also she has gone quite mad.

234
00:09:22,059 --> 00:09:25,059
 Isaac didst inform me how much you searched for Patience

235
00:09:25,059 --> 00:09:27,059
 all those years ago.

236
00:09:27,059 --> 00:09:31,059
 It was a relief on account of how much I did see thee as friends.

237
00:09:31,059 --> 00:09:34,059
 Uh... same.

238
00:09:34,059 --> 00:09:38,019
 Oh, I never had such friends as in the ditch.

239
00:09:38,399 --> 00:09:40,619
 And now we have another chance.

240
00:09:41,319 --> 00:09:41,899
 Huzzah.

241
00:09:42,479 --> 00:09:43,379
 It is ordained.

242
00:09:43,939 --> 00:09:47,679
 We shall spend the remainder of eternity here together.

243
00:09:48,479 --> 00:09:51,439
 Now, it is time for my daily constitutional.

244
00:09:52,399 --> 00:09:55,839
 It took me a century to get my bearings here in the dirt,

245
00:09:55,959 --> 00:09:59,539
 so don't you go wandering off, lest she be lost forever.

246
00:09:59,539 --> 00:10:04,539
 Oh, this sucks.

247
00:10:04,539 --> 00:10:05,539
 Yeah.

248
00:10:05,539 --> 00:10:07,539
 Okay, Flower, you spoke with Patience

249
00:10:07,539 --> 00:10:08,539
 while you were in the well.

250
00:10:08,539 --> 00:10:09,539
 Do you recall her saying anything

251
00:10:09,539 --> 00:10:11,539
 that could help us locate Isaac and Sass?

252
00:10:11,539 --> 00:10:14,539
 Don't love that Flower's memory's load-bearing here.

253
00:10:14,539 --> 00:10:16,539
 Okay, let me think.

254
00:10:16,539 --> 00:10:19,539
 It's interesting, because Patience has taken Isaac,

255
00:10:19,539 --> 00:10:20,539
 and now Sass.

256
00:10:20,539 --> 00:10:22,539
 It's almost like she's abducting everyone

257
00:10:22,539 --> 00:10:24,539
 that was in the ditch with her,

258
00:10:24,539 --> 00:10:26,539
 which just leaves Thor.

259
00:10:26,539 --> 00:10:27,379
 Huh?

260
00:10:27,379 --> 00:10:30,079
 Yeah, she could be coming for you next, big guy.

261
00:10:30,079 --> 00:10:32,379
 The final piece to her creepy little puzzle.

262
00:10:32,379 --> 00:10:34,379
 I'd like to see her try.

263
00:10:34,379 --> 00:10:35,879
 Though not scared.

264
00:10:39,719 --> 00:10:41,879
 Oh, wait, I do remember something about Patience.

265
00:10:41,879 --> 00:10:42,719
